Ask HN: How do I get a personal page design that doesn’t suck?
text:
I just want to focus on content. I want a minimal, fast, legible page that is built from Markdown.

I’ve tried four or five times now. Dozens of hours wasted learning frameworks and testing out themes and designs.

I don’t have thousands of dollars for a designer to come save me. So I’m feeling frustrated and lost at how to get something that’s serviceable so I can move on to the content.

Every blog I see linked on this website seems so nice in comparison!

For reference, my current attempt. I hate it. https://todays.pointless.click/

Ask HN: Startups doing on-device AI/ML
text:
Hi HN, what are the startups being built in the on-device AI/ML space. So, companies that help other companies/devs run/train their models with low-latency/more privacy on device.

I find the field very interesting, so I was wondering if it's possible to build new companies in this space or is it mostly occupied by the hardware developers (Qualcomm, Samsung, Apple, Google, etc.) due to the nature of the low-level software being developed.
